{"questionId":"9067638","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">List <strong>two</strong> components of nucleotides.</span></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em>Any two correct for<strong> [1]</strong>:</em><br>pentose «sugar»<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>deoxyribose ✔</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">phosphate/phosphato «group»/residue of phosphoric acid ✔</span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">NOTE:&nbsp;Accept “−OPO<sub>3</sub><sup>2−</sup>/−OPO<sub>3</sub>H<sup>−</sup>/−OPO<sub>3</sub>H<sub>2</sub>” but <strong>not</strong> “PO<sub>4</sub><sup>3−</sup>”.</span></em></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">«organic» nitrogenous base<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>nucleobase<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>nucleic base<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>purine<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>pyrimidine ✔</span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"> NOTE:&nbsp;Accept the four bases together: “adenine/A, guanine/G, cytosine/C, thymine/T”.<br>Accept names or formulas.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9067638","referenceCode":"19N.3.hl.TZ0.a","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"List two components of nucleotides.","paper":"3","level":"hl","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","B: Biochemistry","B.8 Nucleic acids (HL only)","Options","B: Biochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}